        {
            "date": "2012-03-22 17:29:30", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "With regards to the testsuite for keystone.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The testsuite included in keystone contain both functional and integration tests. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "An example of this keystone integration with keystoneclient, or swift with keystone. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "In order to run these tests, the tests do a git checkout of both swift and keystone when the tests are run. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This make the tests not use what we will have in the archive for swift and keystone (ie make it less static) which is not good for us and less than ideal. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I think we need to have options going forward.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "zulcss", 
            "email": "zulcss"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-22 18:15:22", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Here are the options I see going forward, in preferred order of precedence:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "1. patch the keystone testsuite to work against installed Ubuntu packages (and therefore adding swift and keystoneclient to Build-Depends). This will allow the security, QA and SRU teams to have higher confidence that patches don't break keystone when used against the packages in the archive\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "2. disable the tests that require git and document somewhere (README.Debian?) how the keystone testsuite can be run against Ubuntu installed packages\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "3. do nothing\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I don't really see '3' as an option since keystone is going to be supported for 5 years and upstream git is going to be constantly evolving while the keystone testsuite being used in the package is going to be static. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This means potentially more and more problems when people try to use the integration tests in their personal testing (which we should be doing).\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "'2' is acceptable but far less desirable as it will also require a QRT script.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "jdstrand", 
            "email": "jdstrand"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-22 19:30:16", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I spent some time on this yestreaday, to clarify-\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I don't really see the git checkouts an issue. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " The pending test to swift tests that do this do so only if there is an error importing it from already installed libraries. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " That is, it should be imported locally instead of cloned remotely if we list it with Build-Depends. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " The same should be true of keystoneclient, if its not we can probably patch that easily enough (I'm not able to confirm that the keystoneclient tests are actually running, though, as that would have turned up already)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The bigger problem AFAICS is that the python-swift library used makes an unconditional call to setup a logging handler via /dev/log, which is causing these FTBFS: \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "https://launchpadlibrarian.net/97807065/buildlog_ubuntu-precise-i386.keystone_2012.1%2Bgit201203212030-0ubuntu1_FAILEDTOBUILD.txt.gz\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "We can either disable these swift tests (since they appear to be more integration tests that are actually exercising swift more than keystone), or we can probably carry a small patch to swift as well as a corresponding patch to any test suite that uses it, to make log setup optional.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
